menu "CS1237 Adc Driver"

    config CS1237_DELAY_US
        int "CLK pulse delay (us)"
        range 1 1000
        default 1
        help
            Half-period delay for the CLK signal in microseconds.
            This controls the clock speed of the CS1237 communication.
            Increase this value if you experience communication errors
            due to long wire connections or slow GPIO response times.

    config CS1237_POWER_DOWN_DELAY_US
        int "Power-down delay (us)"
        range 1 1000
        default 100
        help
            Delay in microseconds after setting CLK HIGH for power-down mode.
            The CS1237 requires a minimum delay to enter power-down state.

    config CS1237_POWER_UP_DELAY_US
        int "Power-up delay (us)"
        range 1 1000
        default 10
        help
            Delay in microseconds after setting CLK LOW to wake from power-down.
            The CS1237 requires a minimum delay to stabilize after power-up.

endmenu
